## How to use this worksheet

- **Answer key:** `Yes` / `Partial` / `No` / `N/A — because {{REASON}}`.
- **The N/A rule (hard):** a bare "N/A" is an incomplete answer and causes
  reviewer back-and-forth (baseline:
  `artifact-agentexchange-questionnaire-na-reasons`,
  `fail-incomplete-questionnaire`). Every N/A in this worksheet MUST use the
  compound form `N/A — because {{REASON}}` inline, AND carry a row in the §J
  N/A Register. `/sf-security-review-toolkit:compile-submission` lints for any
  `N/A` not followed by `— because` and for any inline N/A missing its
  register row, and refuses to mark the questionnaire compiled until both pass.
- **Provenance discipline (CONVENTIONS §2):** every answer ends with a
  Provenance line — either `agent-prefilled from {{SOURCE}}` (what an agent
  drafted, from which inputs) or `owner-confirmed {{DATE}}` (a human read it and
  stands behind it). **No agent-prefilled answer goes into the wizard.**
- **Evidence or it didn't happen:** never answer that a scan, test, or
  certification is complete unless the evidence file exists under
  `.security-review/evidence/` and is linked in the answer's Basis line.
- **`Partial` beats an inflated `Yes`.** Reviewers run their own penetration
  test regardless of what you submit (baseline:
  `dast-salesforce-runs-own-pentest`); an answer the pen test contradicts costs
  a review cycle (fee and timeline figures: see `process-review-fee`,
  `process-review-timeline` in the baseline — perishable, confirm in the
  Partner Console).
- **Basis lines are internal.** They trace each answer to code or docs for your
  own audit trail; you do not paste them into the wizard.

